summary: types of people as sanrio characters
title: types of people as sanrio characters
body:
Hello Kitty: Lots of bows, always happy and cheerful, friendly to everyone, just wants to help, loves apples, always singing/dancing, will befriend everyone, rock the primary colors pallette, bakes cookies for all of her friends, super supportive and caring, takes lots of naps.

My Melody: Crybaby but tries their best, loves everything pink and cute, gets scared easily but still watches horror movies, loves to party, eats a lot of sweets, soft but bratty, has the prettiest handwriting.

Kuromi: edgy, probably still on their emo/scene phase, everyday is halloween, pranks everyone, actually really sweet if you get to know them, in love with the moon, reads creepypastas at 3am, 10/10 tsundere.

Pompompurin: the softest of all, loves cocoa, pudding and bread, takes lots of pictures, likes to get cozy and comfy on rainy afternoons, really smart, super talented but wont admit it, full of love, takes their friends on dates at coffee shops.

Cinnamoroll: Very neat and clean, always have what you need (e.x: umbrellas, chapstick, handkierchiefs…), won’t admit they’re wrong, have a bullet journal, loves ice cream, pastel colors + white, have a very organized schedule, never forgets their lunchbox.

Gudetama: Lazy is their middle name, lone wolf, can’t cook, have lots of internet friends, drinks iced tea, loves breakfast, collects stickers, wont admit it but they love hugs, probably needs glasses but wont get them, loves selfcare and skincare.

Aggretsuko: Looks innocent but could demolish you, not very good at emotions, great self control, very professional, sings really well, loves winter, overwork a lot, very competitive (in a good way), daydreams a lot, the adult of their group.

Keroppi: Always outside, loves to swim, was probably a scout, travels a lot, extroverted much, knows species of animals and plants just by looking at them, forgets to eat sometimes, doens’t wear shoes, walks in the rain without their umbrella, drinks a lot of juice.

Badtzmaru: Quiet and reserved, says they don’t have friends but really cherishes the ones they have, tries to look harsh and actually accomplishes it, will call you a pain but will never stop helping you (even if you don’t ask), sighs a lot.

Little Twin Stars: Always close to their best friend, will never do you wrong, loves rainbows, hides their feelings, plays on their phone a lot, has an aesthetic instagram acc, has seen every show and movie on netflix, is secretly good at sports.

summary: Aggretsuko: We Wish You a Metal Christmas Review
body:
Aggretsuko: We Wish You a Metal Christmas Review

I really felt disappointed in general. First if all, twenty minutes doesn’t seem like enough time for a holiday special. It felt rushed and more like, “Hey here’s a little filler until Season 2”. I’m sort of surprised that they got away with actually mentioning Instagram but then again it’s a Netflix series. I can see getting hyped up about Xmas eve plans. I’m also bummed about Retsuko turning down Haida. But looking back on it, she doesn’t really know what she wants yet. I hope they build more on that in Season 2. I also feel that Fenneko may have feelings for Haida and that could be a possible conflict on the horizon. In conclusion, if you haven’t seen the special, just skip it and wait for Season 2. But unless you’re going through withdrawals then knock yourself out.

title: Goddamn
body:
Okay so I have been pretty busy lately and by busy I mean watching tons of shows/anime I have been meaning to watch. 

And I just finished this little animation called Aggretsuko on Netflix… I only have two words. 

Fucking badass. 

Okay, so I don’t know if you all already know this about me but I love all kinds of metal. If I think it sounds good then I’ll love it. (Obviously Grace) xD But this show has all the requirements I MUST have to LOVE a show. In order to get me to love a show it must have a variety of characters, different personalities, maturing characters, romance, life lessons, able to appeal to a variety of ages, cuteness, badassness, and (one I didn’t think I needed), death metal. xDDDDDD I fucking love that little cat. I can relate to her as an adult but as well as a younger audience on the problems she faces. This show gives you lessons on life, love, mental illness, and social standards. If you can’t tell what I’m talking about, watch the show until you see it. XD She gets angry and once she’s filled with rage she’ll take out her anger by singing to Death Metal (which is one of the darkest types of metals out there) and she fucking kills it. Like when I first saw the show on Netflix I thought it was going to be a little “Kawaii” type shit. Well honey, I had a big storm coming. lol I love this little dumb ass. There are so many things I could learn from a little animated cat created by the same company as Hello Kitty. xD And the metal in this show isn’t even wack. Like ya girl was headbanging throughout all the times a song came on. Man, I am just blown away. So yeah. Give it a watch, I seriously recommend it. If you don’t like metal now you’ll like it after this show. jajaja (yeah I use the Mexican style of hahah @ me tho) lol

Also, listening/singing to metal music to relieve stress/anger is a great way to cope. I do it all the time and it works. Never thought I’d see that in a show like this. Seriously iconic. Thumbs up from me!
